-- Emirates Will Order More Aircraft at July Air Show, Dubai Ruler Tells CNN
-- Arif Sharif
-- 2010-06-23T05:24:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-23/emirates-will-order-more-aircraft-at-july-air-show-dubai-ruler-tells-cnn.html

          
          
             Emirates, the Dubai government-owned
airline, will place orders for more planes at the Farnborough
Air Show in July to meet travel demand,  Sheikh Mohammed Bin Rashid  Al Maktoum told  CNN .  
 The growth in passenger numbers and tourists at Dubai is
“very big,” Sheikh Mohammed, Dubai’s ruler said in the TV
interview to be broadcast on Friday.  
 A Dubai government spokeswoman confirmed the comments made
in the interview, which was reported by  Emirates Business 24/7 .  
 Emirates placed an order to buy 32 A380 jets from Airbus
SAS on June 8 valued at $11.5 billion, taking its total order
for the superjumbo to 90.  
